 for bestpractices and # User Authentication & Authorization

## Overview
Build a secure, scalable authentication and authorization system for Roam Resort that supports:
- Email/password authentication with session persistence
- Email verification with expiry and resend rate limiting
- Password reset via token-based flow
- Role-based access control (RBAC) for Guests, Hosts, and Concierge
- JWT or secure cookie-based sessions with HTTPOnly, Secure tokens
- Admin-facing RBAC middleware protecting host/admin pages and API endpoints
- Connected pages for profile, password reset, host dashboard, email verification, and login/signup flows
- Strong runtime safety: guard against null/undefined for all array operations and API responses, initialize useState with proper defaults, and normalize Supabase-like results to arrays

Project context: Roam Resort – Inquiry-Based Luxury Resort Platform. Primary flows include user registration, stay inquiry submission, host listings with statuses (Draft/Live), concierge admin flows, and manual payment reconciliation. Ensure the frontend and backend integrate cleanly with a Postgres database, password hashing, token management, and secure session handling. Implement accessible, responsive UI following the provided design language and color system.

---

## Components to Build

1) User Authentication Core
- User table: id, email (unique), password_hash, role (guest|host|concierge), is_email_verified (bool), created_at, updated_at
- Email verification tokens: token, user_id, expires_at, used (bool)
- Password reset tokens: token, user_id, expires_at, used (bool)
- Sessions or JWT: access_token, refresh_token (or stateless JWT with refresh mechanism)
- RBAC middleware (server-side): restrict endpoints by role and authenticated status
- Email sending service with rate limiting for verification and password reset

2) Frontend Routes / Pages
- Login / Signup (page_010)
- Email Verification Landing (page_008)
- Password Reset (page_009)
- User Profile / My Inquiries (page_006)
- Host Dashboard (Listings List) (page_007)
- Admin/Concierge tools (internal views) as needed (page_013)

3) Frontend Components
- Auth forms: login, signup, password reset request, password reset
- Email verification flow: landing view upon token click
- Profile dashboard: profile editing, inquiry history list, preferences
- Inquiry display and status indicators (read-only for hosts)
- Host dashboard: listings list with Draft/Live status, summary of inquiries per listing
- Listings editor form (Host): image upload, metadata, publish toggle (Draft/Live)
- Global RBAC-aware routing and guards
- Toasts/notifications for success/failure
- Input validation with real-time feedback

4) Backend APIs
- User CRUD and auth routes
  - POST /auth/register
  - POST /auth/login
  - POST /auth/logout
  - POST /auth/verify-email
  - POST /auth/resend-verification
  - POST /auth/password-reset-request
  - POST /auth/password-reset
  - GET /auth/me (profile)
- Tokens and sessions
  - POST /session/refresh (if using refresh tokens)
- Email verification tokens
  - GET /verify-email?token=... (landing)
- Password reset
  - GET/POST endpoints to validate token and set new password
- RBAC-protected resources
  - Host listings: CRUD (create/update/draft-live), read-only inquiries per listing
  - Inquiries: create (guest), read (concierge/admin/host with permission), update statuses (concierge)
  - Payment status reconciliation (admin)
- Data models for:
  - Users
  - Listings (host-owned)
  - Inquiries
  - Payments (manual reconciliation metadata)
  - Tokens (verification/password reset)
- Security features
  - Password hashing with bcrypt or argon2
  - Secure token generation (crypto.randomBytes, JWTs with proper claims)
  - Token expiry handling
  - HTTPOnly, Secure cookies or robust JWT with refresh tokens
  - Rate limiting for verification/resend endpoints

5) Data Modeling and Data Layer
- Postgres schema (normalized):
  - users(id PK, email UNIQUE, password_hash, role ENUM('guest','host','concierge'), is_email_verified BOOLEAN, created_at TIMESTAMPTZ, updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ)
  - listings(id PK, host_id FK -> users.id, title, description, location, price, publish_status ENUM('Draft','Live'), created_at, updated_at, cover_image_url, etc.)
  - inquiries(id PK, guest_id FK -> users.id, listing_id FK -> listings.id, stay_dates, guests, message, status ENUM('New','Contacted','Deposit Paid','Confirmed'), created_at, updated_at)
  - verification_tokens(id PK, user_id FK, token TEXT, expires_at TIMESTAMPTZ, used BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE)
  - reset_tokens(id PK, user_id FK, token TEXT, expires_at TIMESTAMPTZ, used BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE)
  - sessions(id PK, user_id FK, access_token TEXT, refresh_token TEXT, expires_at TIMESTAMPTZ)
  - payments(id PK, inquiry_id FK, amount, status ENUM('Pending','Paid','Failed'), external_reference, created_at)
- Validation and constraints
  - Ensure foreign keys and cascading where appropriate
  - Indexes on email, tokens, status fields for performance

6) Integration Layer
- Frontend-backend contracts: RESTful endpoints with JSON payloads
- Authentication middleware on backend to parse tokens, set req.user
- RBAC middleware to enforce access in protected routes
- Email service integration (mockable in tests)
- Stripe Connect integration placeholder for future payments (no real charges in V1)
- Supabase-like results guard patterns for any data fetch (even if not using Supabase)

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks: React (with hooks), Next.js or equivalent, or a similar SPA/SSR setup
- State management: useState/useEffect for isolated components; optionally a context/store for auth state
- Routing: protected routes that redirect based on role; guard components
- UI Components:
  - AuthForm: handles login/signup with client-side validation
  - PasswordResetForm: new password entry after token validation
  - EmailVerificationLanding: shows success/failure states
  - ProfileDashboard: editable profile fields, password change, inquiry history with pagination
  - HostDashboard: list of host listings with statuses; per-listing read-only inquiry summaries
  - ListingsEditor: form to create/edit listings with image uploads (progress, previews)
  - InquiryList: for concierge/admin with status filters and export
- Data safety:
  - All API responses normalized: data ?? [] or Array.isArray checks
  - Safeguards in data display: (items ?? []).map(...)
  - Initialize arrays in state: useState<MyType[]>([])
- Accessibility: aria-labels, keyboard navigable, proper contrast per color system
- Validation:
  - Client-side input validation with clear error messages
  - Password strength rules
  - Email format validation
- Security-conscious UI behaviors:
  - Do not expose password hashes
  - Do not leak internal IDs in client code beyond necessary
- Performance and UX:
  - Debounced validation where appropriate
  - Loading skeletons for lists
  - Clear success/error toasts
- Design system adherence:
  - Implement UI using the provided color palette, typography, and components as described
  - Card, navigation, and form components with defined hover and focus states

### Backend
- Language: Node.js (Express/Kestrel equivalent) or a framework of choice
- Database access: PostgreSQL with an ORM (Prisma, TypeORM) or plain query builder
- Endpoints:
  - Authentication
    - POST /api/auth/register
    - POST /api/auth/login
    - POST /api/auth/logout
    - POST /api/auth/resend-verification
    - POST /api/auth/verify-email (or GET with token)
  - Password management
    - POST /api/auth/password-reset-request
    - POST /api/auth/password-reset
  - User profile
    - GET /api/users/me
    - PATCH /api/users/me (update profile)
  - Listings (Host)
    - GET /api/hosts/listings
    - POST /api/hosts/listings
    - PATCH /api/hosts/listings/:id
    - GET /api/hosts/listings/:id/inquiries (read-only)
  - Inquiries (Guest/Concierge)
    - POST /api/inquiries
    - GET /api/inquiries/:id
    - GET /api/inquiries (admin/concierge)
    - PATCH /api/inquiries/:id (status update, internal notes for concierge)
  - Payments (placeholder for manual flow)
    - POST /api/payments/confirm
    - GET /api/payments/:id
  - Tokens (internal)
    - Helpers for generating/validating tokens
- Security:
  - Hash passwords with bcrypt or argon2
  - Store and validate verification/reset tokens with expiry timestamps
  - Use HTTPOnly, Secure cookies or robust JWT with proper expiration
  - Implement rate limiting on sensitive endpoints (verify/resend, password reset)
  - RBAC middleware enforcing roles on protected routes
- Validation:
  - Server-side validation for all inputs
  - Normalize API responses: { data: ..., error?: ... } and ensure arrays default to []
- Data safety:
  - Guard against null results, e.g., const listings = Array.isArray(data?.listings) ? data.listings : []
  - Use nullish coalescing in responses and logs

### Integration
- Connect frontend routes to backend APIs with consistent error handling
- Centralize auth header/token refresh logic
- Use shared utilities for:
  - API request wrappers with timeouts and error mapping
  - Role-based redirects and access checks
  - Data normalization helpers (ensure arrays, safe maps)
- Ensure all pages (page_006, page_007, page_008, page_009, page_010, page_013) render conditionally based on authentication and role
- Implement email verification flow where clicking verification link routes to Email Verification Landing page
- Ensure session persistence across page reloads and navigation

---

## User Experience Flow

1) Guest visits homepage
- Sees destinations and a prominent "Request a Stay" CTA
- Clicks CTA -> redirected to Login/Signup (page_010)

2) Guest signs up or logs in
- If new, creates account with email/password, selects role “Guest”
- Receives verification email; clicks verification link
- Landing view confirms verification and prompts to complete profile

3) Guest submits an inquiry
- Auth gate ensures login
- Fills stay details form (destination, dates, guests, notes)
- Submits; receives confirmation screen
- Concierge may respond with a Stripe connect payment link for deposit or manual payment workflow

4) Host signs in to Host Dashboard (page_007)
- Sees Listings List with status (Draft/Live)
- Creates/edits listings with images and content
- Can view related inquiries (read-only) per listing

5) Concierge signs in (Admin)
- Views all inquiries, updates status (New -> Contacted -> Deposit Paid -> Confirmed)
- Adds internal notes
- Exports inquiries as CSV
- Reconciles payments manually offline

6) Password Reset flow (page_009)
- User requests password reset via email
- Receives tokenized link; lands on Password Reset page
- Submits new password; automatic login or redirect to login

7) Email verification (page_008)
- User clicks link from email
- Lands on page confirming verification and signup completion
- Redirects to appropriate flow based on role (Guest/Host/Concierge)

8) Profile / My Inquiries (page_006)
- Authenticated user can edit profile, update preferences
- View inquiries history with status and details
- Update notification settings and preferences

---

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: [Schema details]
- users: id, email, password_hash, role, is_email_verified, created_at, updated_at
- listings: id, host_id, title, description, location, price, publish_status (Draft|Live), cover_image_url, created_at, updated_at
